But I'm here to offer something a little different.

18
00:00:55,596 --> 00:00:55,896
I've been...

19
00:00:56,950 --> 00:01:01,192
sort of circulating around in the game industry as a historian of this industry for some time,

20
00:01:01,292 --> 00:01:07,034
and it's kind of led me to compile some thoughts about how I think these two, in some ways,

21
00:01:07,094 --> 00:01:13,057
alternate professions can learn to speak better to one another if we get some foundation in what

22
00:01:13,077 --> 00:01:21,081
it is that history involves and what it does. So, all right, I'm gonna go. Okay, so I want to begin

23
00:01:22,521 --> 00:01:25,383
by looking at some stuff that we've saved over time.

24
00:01:27,372 --> 00:01:29,836
So you may recognize this as the Bayeux Tapestry,

25
00:01:30,016 --> 00:01:32,440
an embroidered cloth 230 feet long,

26
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,663
depicting the Norman invasion of England

27
00:01:34,743 --> 00:01:35,604
by William the Conqueror.

28
00:01:35,624 --> 00:01:37,607
It was constructed in the 11th century.

29
00:01:37,647 --> 00:01:38,849
It's made of wool and linen,

30
